                   order=df['Species'].value_counts(ascending=False).index);
        
abs_values = df['Species'].value_counts(ascending=False)
rel_values = df['Species'].value_counts(ascending=False, normalize=True).values * 100
lbls = [f'{p[0]} ({p[1]:.0f}%)' for p in zip(abs_values, rel_values)]

#REGRESI LINEAR

x = df['Length1'] 
y = df['Weight']

slope, intercept, r, p, std_err = stats.linregress(x, y)

def fungsiLinear(x):
 return slope * x + intercept

modelLinear = list(map(fungsiLinear, x))

plt.scatter(x, y, color = 'Green')
plt.plot(x, slope * x + intercept, c='red')
plt.title("Regresi Linear")
plt.xlabel("Panjang Ikan")
plt.ylabel("Berat Ikan")
plt.show()

#Training Data

train, test = train_test_split(df, test_size = 0.3)# in this our main data is split into train and test
# the attribute test_size=0.3 splits the data into 70% and 30% ratio. train=70% and test=30%
print('TRAIN SHAPE :',train.shape)
print('TEST SHAPE :',test.shape)

X_train = train[['Height','Width']]# taking the training data features
Y_train = train.Species # output of our training data
X_test = test[['Height','Width']] # taking test data features
Y_test = test.Species #output value of test data

TRAIN SHAPE : (111, 7)
TEST SHAPE : (48, 7)

In [ ]:
#R2 Pada Regresi Linear

slope, intercept, r, p, std_err = stats.linregress(x, y)
r2Linear = r*r
akurasi_reg_linear = round(r2Linear * 100, 2)

print('Nilai r pada regresi linear adalah', r)
print('Nilai R2 pada regresi linear adalah ', r2Linear)
print('Akurasi dari Regresi Linear adalah', akurasi_reg_linear, "%")

Nilai r pada regresi linear adalah 0.9157117160312036
Nilai R2 pada regresi linear adalah  0.8385279468768116
Akurasi dari Regresi Linear adalah 83.85 %
